question: Which country houses the "National Reserve of Saint Bartholomew"?
explanation: Nature Reserve of Siant Bartholomew is an IUCN Category II national park located in the Saint Barthelemy island which is an overseas collectivity of France in the French West Indies region of the Caribbean Sea. This reserve is the habitat of several bird and coral species. The key bird species recorded in this reserve are frown booby, laughing gull, royal tern, and common tern.
